	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, there's no technical requirement that the "slots" should be the same size, so your emulator/whatever shouldn't rely on that. In fact MMC5 for example has a mode (mode #2) where one bank is 16K and other two are 8K: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC5#PRG_mode_.28.245100.29">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC5 ... .245100.29</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


